    <name>Instructors Need a Growth Mindset, Too</name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{7266adea-edb5-4692-8894-1de5f91fac6a}{172}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Both math anxiety and mindset are transferable: an instructor who experiences math anxiety and has&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;a fixed mindset may inadvertently trigger both in learners. As growth mindset researchers, Dweck&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;and Leggett (1988) state,&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{7266adea-edb5-4692-8894-1de5f91fac6a}{175}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;“Teachers with fixed mindsets attribute students’ achievements to innate intelligence, whereas&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;those with growth mindsets are more likely to perceive students’ achievements as opportunities to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;further improve their competence.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{7266adea-edb5-4692-8894-1de5f91fac6a}{178}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;We as teachers can inadvertently set up a cycle of ineffective action and reaction. Our own fixed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;mindsets, in this case with anxiety or negativity about math, and teacher perception of student ability&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;in math, may increase poor math performance and demotivate students. An important first step for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;breaking the cycle is for instructors to become more aware of their own mindset&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9757@$" target="_blank"&gt;(&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9757@$" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Appleton et al.,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;2017)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{7266adea-edb5-4692-8894-1de5f91fac6a}{178}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Try%20It%20Yourself.png" alt="" width="68" height="66" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Try it Yourself:&lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9763@$&amp;amp;forceview=1"&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9763@$&amp;amp;forceview=1" target="_blank"&gt;Help adult learners assess their own learning mindset&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider%20wave.png" alt="Divider wave" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
